	<Title>
		Put a leash on anger
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Do you find yourself fuming when someone cuts you off in traffic? Anger is a normal and even healthy emotion, but it&apos;s important to deal with it in a positive way. Uncontrolled anger can take a toll on your health and your relationships. To get your anger under control, follow these steps: 1.Take a timeout from the situation. 2. When you&apos;re calm, express your concern. 3. Use humor to defuse tensions. It may be challenging at first, but with time and effort, healthy responses may come naturally.&lt;/p&gt;
